<org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-rqVoRkzZ2MThc2cxhNcCkA" name="measurement_specification,_RaLCMP1IEd20w98rSqT2fg" guid="-rqVoRkzZ2MThc2cxhNcCkA" changeDate="2009-04-02T13:53:02.108-0700" version="7.5.0">
  <purpose>&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        To document the detail design of the measures&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        To document the details of the Measurement Infrastructure, including the overall topology and detail configuration.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></purpose>
  <impactOfNotHaving>This is a critical artifact; organizations must have a place to store the measurement design and configuration information.</impactOfNotHaving>
  <briefOutline>&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Detailed Metrics&lt;/strong> - each of the measures and indicators&amp;nbsp;defined in detail, including such&#xD;
        aspects as the frequency and format of the data collection as well as the data interpretation.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Detailed Measurement Infrastructure&lt;/strong> - software and hardware is identified that will be used in the&#xD;
        collection, manipulation, storage, and the reporting of&amp;nbsp;the measures and indicators. Within this artifact tool&#xD;
        configuration information will be documented. A topology diagram is suggested to document the hardware and software&#xD;
        components and their relationships.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></briefOutline>
  <representationOptions>This information is normally captured in a word processing document, Excel spreadsheet with the topology diagram&#xD;
illustrated in a UML diagram.</representationOptions>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription>
